SUMMARY:Community Benefits Advisory Council
LOCATION:Tampa \, FL United States
DESCRIPTION:COMMUNITY BENEFITS ADVISORY COUNCIL NOTICE OF PUBLIC MEETING D
 ATE: July 15 th \, 2026 TIME: 3 p.m. LOCATION: Tampa Municipal Office Buil
 ding 2 nd Floor Conference Room 306 E Jackson\, St.\, Tampa\, FL 33602 MEE
 TING PURPOSE: The purpose of this public meeting of the Community Benefits
  Advisory Council (CBAC) is to discuss the draft Community Benefits Agreem
 ent to be presented to City Council regarding proposed community benefits 
 associated with the Sanchez y Haya Project. Community benefits discussed m
 ay include\, but are not limited to\, activities in the following areas: E
 nvironmental resiliency and sustainability Public infrastructure and publi
 c realm improvements Equitable economic opportunities and small business s
 upport Historic preservation and adaptive reuse initiatives Mobility\, ped
 estrian\, bicycle\, and transit improvements Public art\, cultural preserv
 ation\, community gathering spaces\, and neighborhood amenities Members of
  the public will have an opportunity to provide public comments during the
  meeting. We expect that the draft agreement will be ready for review by J
 uly 7 th \, 2026. If you would like to receive a copy for review\, prior t
 o the meeting please email Amanda Alfarah at Amanda.alfarahtampagov.net (m
 ailto:Amanda.alfarahtampagov.net). VIRTUAL PARTICIPATION OPTION Individual
 s who are unable to attend in person may participate virtually using the M
 icrosoft Teams information below: Join: https:teams.microsoft.commeet29416
